1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:02,665
Start with two independent axes.

2
00:00:02,615 --> 00:00:09,375
Human intensity measures how much continuous judgment, taste, negotiation, or context only you can provide.

3
00:00:09,375 --> 00:00:15,903
Agent intensity measures how much searching, transforming, coordinating, or tool use the AI can perform.

4
00:00:15,903 --> 00:00:18,192
These axes are not opposites.

5
00:00:18,192 --> 00:00:23,288
A task can require high human intensity and high agent intensity at the same time.

6
00:00:23,288 --> 00:00:31,567
A product launch, for example, may need constant human calls while an agent gathers evidence, updates artifacts, and checks dependencies.

7
00:00:31,567 --> 00:00:34,000
Now add four routing questions.

8
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:36,634
Is the desired output already specific?

9
00:00:36,634 --> 00:00:39,759
How much human judgment must stay inside the work?

10
00:00:39,759 --> 00:00:42,682
Can success be checked with observable evidence?

11
00:00:42,682 --> 00:00:45,125
And what happens if the AI is wrong?

12
00:00:45,125 --> 00:00:49,259
Those questions are more useful than asking whether a model is capable.

13
00:00:49,259 --> 00:00:51,701
Capability is only one input.

14
00:00:51,701 --> 00:00:59,086
A capable model can still be a poor fit when the task is ambiguous, the evidence is weak, or a mistake has a large consequence.

15
00:00:59,086 --> 00:01:02,509
The Microsoft research makes the human boundary visible.

16
00:01:02,509 --> 00:01:09,750
Eighty-six percent of respondents treated AI output as a starting point and still saw themselves as responsible for the final result.

17
00:01:09,750 --> 00:01:12,519
The important move is not removing the human.

18
00:01:12,519 --> 00:01:15,942
It is placing human attention where it changes the outcome.

19
00:01:15,942 --> 00:01:18,673
So draw the map before you choose the tool.

20
00:01:18,673 --> 00:01:24,721
Put human intensity on one axis, agent intensity on the other, and route the current phase of the task.

21
00:01:24,721 --> 00:01:29,086
Do not label an entire project once and assume the mode will never change.

22
00:01:29,086 --> 00:01:33,259
First, Human intensity and agent intensity are independent.

23
00:01:33,259 --> 00:01:37,221
Second, Choose from task conditions, not AI ambition.

24
00:01:37,221 --> 00:01:40,250
Third, Outcome ownership stays with the human.
